Kamarudeen Ogundele, Abuja The governors of the 36 states met last night in Abuja seeking partnership for housing scheme in their states. The meeting which was ongoing as of the time of filing this report was presided over by their Chairman and Governor of Ekiti State, Dr Kayode Fayemi. The meeting held under the umbrella of the Nigeria Governors Forum. The governors are aloso expected to discuss further on the deductions for bailout funds. Also at the meeting were governors of Ekiti, Osun, Ondo, Jigawa, Kebbi, Nasarawa, Plateau, Yobe, Niger, Delta, Kaduna. Gombe, Borno, Oyo,  Kogi, Anambra, Enugu and Kano  states were represented by their deputies. The Federal Government had in August said a committee had been put in place to facilitate recovery of N614bn given to 35 states. A total of 35 states benefited from the facility, and each state is expected to pay back the equivalent of N17.5bn.  The N614bn was a conditional budget support provided by the Central Bank of Nigeria to help states pay salaries gratuities and pensions. Copyright PUNCH.
